# Front door for a SPLIT setup on your LAN: Caddy + piHole on one box, your
# services on another. (Internet-facing? Use Caddyfile.frontdoor-public.example.)
#
# piHole points every *.<your-domain> at this box. This Caddy adds HTTPS and
# forwards each request to the services box's Caddy, which hands it to the right
# container. Services come and go without ever editing this file.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Services box: run the stack as usual (its Caddy serves :443).
#   2. This box: enable caddy + pihole, then `./existential.sh run` (creates the
#      cert in hosting/caddy/certs/ — run it on both boxes).
#   3. In .env.shared: EXIST_PEER_HOST_IP = services box LAN IP, EXIST_DOMAIN = your domain.
#   4. Use this file and restart:
#        cp hosting/caddy/Caddyfile.frontdoor-lan.example hosting/caddy/Caddyfile
#        docker compose up -d
#
# Cert: self-signed by default — install the CA on your devices once (see
# Caddyfile.exist.Caddyfile). To use your own real cert instead, drop the cert + key
# into hosting/caddy/certs/ as internal.pem / internal-key.pem.

(error_handling) {
  handle_errors {
    root * /var/www/html
    file_server
    rewrite * /error.html
  }
}

(internal_tls) {
  tls /etc/caddy/certs/internal.pem /etc/caddy/certs/internal-key.pem
}

# Send every *.<domain> to the services box's Caddy. It serves the same domain and
# cert, so we skip re-checking the cert on this internal hop.
*.{$CADDY_DOMAIN} {
  import internal_tls
  import error_handling
  reverse_proxy https://{$EXIST_PEER_HOST_IP} {
    header_up Host {host}
    transport http {
      tls
      tls_insecure_skip_verify
    }
  }
}
